# user defined functions

file <- function(url){
  file <- read_csv(url)
  return (file)
}

rename_primary <- function(data){
  data <-
    data %>%
    rename(
      name = Name,
      platform = Platform,
      year = Year_of_Release,
      genre = Genre,
      publisher = Publisher,
      na_sales = NA_Sales,
      eu_sales = EU_Sales,
      jp_sales= JP_Sales,
      other_sales = Other_Sales,
      global_sales =  Global_Sales,
      critic_score = Critic_Score,
      critic_count = Critic_Count,
      user_score = User_Score,
      user_count = User_Count,
      rating = Rating
    )
  return (data)
}

rename_developer <- function(data){
  data <-
    data %>%
    rename(
      name = Name,
      platform = Platform,
      year = Year_of_Release,
      genre = Genre,
      publisher = Publisher,
      rating = Rating,
      developer = Developer
    )
  return (data)
}

Import the Data & Inspections

library(readr)
Primary <- read_csv("Video_Game_Sales_as_of_Jan_2017.csv")
head(Primary)
Developer <- read_csv("GameDeveloper.csv")
head(Developer)

Change the Column Names to Lower-case

Developer <-
  rename_developer(Developer)
Primary <- 
  rename_primary(Primary)
head(Primary)
head(Developer)

Clean Data and Merge two datasets together

Developer_clean <-
  Developer %>%
  select(name,developer)
Games_final <-
  Primary %>%
  left_join(Developer_clean,by=c("name"="name"))
Games_final <-
  Games_final %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  distinct()
head(Games_final)

Data Visualization

SalesByYear <-
  Games_final %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarise(total = sum(global_sales)) %>%
  arrange((year))
SalesByYear %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = total)) +
  ggtitle("Sales By Year") +
  geom_line()

SalesByPlatform <-
  Games_final %>%
  group_by(platform) %>%
  summarise(total=sum(global_sales))
SalesByPlatform %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = platform)) +
  ggtitle("Sales By Year and Platform") +
  geom_bar(aes(weight = total))

Sales_platform_user_score <-
  party::ctree(
    global_sales ~ critic_score + user_score,
    data=Games_final)
Games_final %>%
  mutate(probability=as.numeric(predict(Sales_platform_user_score)),
         likelihood =
           ifelse(global_sales,
                  probability,
                  1-probability)) %>%
  summarise(log_likelihood = sum(log(likelihood)))
DecisionTree <- rpart( global_sales ~ critic_score + critic_count + user_score + user_count, data = Games_final)
prp(DecisionTree)

Sales_By_Year_Genre_Ranking <-
  Games_final %>%
  group_by(genre,rating,year) %>%
  summarise(total = sum(global_sales))
Sales_By_Year_Genre_Ranking %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year,y = total)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = genre)) +
  ggtitle("Sales By Year & Genre & Ranking") +
  facet_wrap(~rating)

SalesByDeveloper <-
  Games_final %>%
  group_by(developer) %>%
  summarise(total = sum(global_sales)) %>%
  arrange(desc(total)) %>%
  head(7)
SalesByDeveloper %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = developer)) +
  geom_bar(aes(weight = total)) +
  ggtitle("Sales By Top 7 Developers")
